<plot>You can be tried for the same crime twice-on PAX TV's "Second Verdict," the next generation of court shows. Audiences will be taken through the compelling facts of real-life trials in broadcast television's first primetime courtroom reality series, where a mock jury decides if justice was served. In "Second Verdict," real felony cases from compelling trials that permitted cameras in the courtroom are presented to a panel. Unaware of the actual jury's verdict, the mock jury votes, and the show's hard-nosed, legal expert will reveal the actual verdict while giving new insight on whether justice was served. Was it a case of mistaken identity or did the time fit the crime?</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?483393</url></doc>
